</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Bridges" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Long Exposure" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The historic Tohka Saikan Chinese restaurant (1924) and the Shijo Ohashi bridge over the Kamogawa river, in a long exposure at dusk. 1924年建築の由緒ある中華料理店「東華菜館」と、鴨川に架かる四条大橋を、夕暮れ時の長時間露光で捉えた写真だ。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSCF1821_edit_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSCF1821_edit_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Morning on the Togetsu Bridge・渡月橋の朝</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260509/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Morning on the Togetsu Bridge・渡月橋の朝" /><published>2026-05-09T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-09T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/togetsukyo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260509/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Stopping to take a picture of the beautiful view in Arashiyama this morning. Me too.
</p>
